WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:04.538
♪ ♪

00:15.316 --> 00:17.551
[chickens clucking]

00:34.202 --> 00:36.504
[dog barking]

00:41.875 --> 00:44.278
♪ ♪

00:47.781 --> 00:52.153
[zipper zips,
belt buckle jingles]

00:53.754 --> 00:54.722
[briefcase closes]

01:21.482 --> 01:23.417
[men speaking Spanish]

01:23.451 --> 01:25.653
[man calls out indistinctly]

01:30.224 --> 01:31.392
[rooster crows]

01:31.425 --> 01:33.227
[dog barks]

02:22.310 --> 02:24.578
♪ ♪

02:52.606 --> 02:55.476
♪ ♪

03:08.356 --> 03:10.891
[TV playing]

03:14.562 --> 03:15.663
[clunk]

03:27.775 --> 03:29.410
[cocks gun]

03:32.446 --> 03:34.248
[chuckles dryly]

03:57.037 --> 03:59.773
♪ ♪

04:22.896 --> 04:25.299
♪ ♪

04:38.379 --> 04:42.316
♪ ♪

04:54.595 --> 04:57.565
♪ ♪

05:02.636 --> 05:04.605
Griselda Blanco.

05:07.040 --> 05:08.075
Her file wouldn't cross my desk

05:08.108 --> 05:09.643
at the D.E.A.

05:09.677 --> 05:12.079
until long after she arrived
in America.

05:14.382 --> 05:18.586
She made it to New York in 1972.

05:18.619 --> 05:21.789
She was small time at first,
a petty criminal...

05:25.926 --> 05:27.027
just trying to make ends meet

05:27.060 --> 05:31.499
for her husband
and her three little boys.

05:33.867 --> 05:37.971
[slicing paper]

05:42.776 --> 05:44.645
Now, it turns out
she was a natural

05:44.678 --> 05:46.780
at counterfeiting passports...

05:48.849 --> 05:51.852
and the local drug dealers
kept her busy,

05:51.885 --> 05:55.456
Especially Alberto Bravo.

06:01.629 --> 06:04.131
[door opens, footsteps approach]

06:04.164 --> 06:05.433
[man]: Let's
have some rum.

06:05.466 --> 06:07.435
[another man chuckles]

06:08.936 --> 06:10.170
Griselda!

06:10.203 --> 06:12.406
Where is the rum?

06:21.715 --> 06:23.984
Ah. She found it.
Bingo.

06:24.017 --> 06:26.153
The boys will be up
in two hours, Carlos.

06:26.186 --> 06:27.788
And you.

06:27.821 --> 06:29.790
Why do you encourage
him, Alberto? Huh?

06:29.823 --> 06:31.158
Ah, it's simple.

06:31.191 --> 06:33.594
Because I get to see you.

06:33.627 --> 06:35.429
Where are the goods?
He doesn't have all day.

06:51.879 --> 06:54.114
These are fantastic.

06:54.147 --> 06:55.616
You only get better, Griselda.

06:55.649 --> 06:56.717
Well, somebody

06:56.750 --> 06:58.952
has to keep food on the table.

06:58.986 --> 07:01.054
Hey, you shut your mouth, woman.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.824
Well...
I should get going,

07:03.857 --> 07:05.893
as much as I would love to stay,

07:05.926 --> 07:07.160
but remember...

07:07.194 --> 07:08.762
[both]:...If you ever...

07:08.796 --> 07:11.699
...Want to make real money,
give you a call.

07:11.732 --> 07:13.534
Hilarious, Alberto.

07:13.567 --> 07:14.468
As always.

07:15.536 --> 07:17.538
[chuckles]
"Hilarious."

07:34.688 --> 07:37.658
♪ ♪

08:35.582 --> 08:36.750
Griselda.

08:38.686 --> 08:40.287
You should know...

08:40.320 --> 08:43.090
I won't be
one of your mules, Alberto.

08:44.758 --> 08:46.760
Mules are quiet and dumb.

08:46.794 --> 08:47.695
You don't exactly

08:47.728 --> 08:48.896
fit the bill.

08:48.929 --> 08:50.197
Exactly.

08:50.230 --> 08:51.599
They're...

08:51.632 --> 08:53.300
farm workers.

08:53.333 --> 08:55.669
Peasants.

08:55.703 --> 08:57.170
So?

08:57.204 --> 08:58.606
So...

08:58.639 --> 09:02.142
smuggling is cosmetic.

09:02.175 --> 09:04.745
What's on the surface.

09:04.778 --> 09:08.616
You look good, you do good, no?

09:08.649 --> 09:10.283
In life.

09:10.317 --> 09:13.120
I suppose.

09:15.823 --> 09:18.325
Use women, pretty women.

09:19.793 --> 09:23.130
Models, even.

09:28.268 --> 09:29.837
Looks good, no?

09:29.870 --> 09:31.304
Mm-mm.

09:31.338 --> 09:33.140
Huh?

09:33.173 --> 09:38.178
Do I look like
some poor, uneducated smuggler?

09:38.211 --> 09:40.614
No.

09:43.383 --> 09:46.253
I have a kilo on me right now.

09:47.420 --> 09:50.891
Well, flour,
but you get the idea.

09:57.164 --> 09:59.867
I found these at the pharmacy,

09:59.900 --> 10:02.870
filled them with flour,

10:02.903 --> 10:05.105
sewed them into my bra,

10:05.138 --> 10:06.774
my girdle,

10:06.807 --> 10:08.175
and I put the rest in my heels.

10:08.208 --> 10:09.677
[laughs, incredulous]

10:09.710 --> 10:10.711
You're joking.

10:10.744 --> 10:12.713
No.

10:12.746 --> 10:15.849
We'll get a hotel room
after lunch.

10:15.883 --> 10:18.118
Only to show you.

10:18.151 --> 10:19.753
[chuckles dryly]

10:21.154 --> 10:22.222
[laughs]

10:22.255 --> 10:24.958
♪ ♪

10:35.435 --> 10:38.205
[laughing]

10:48.481 --> 10:51.051
You look nice.

10:51.084 --> 10:53.186
What's the occasion?

10:53.220 --> 10:55.122
Why aren't you at work?

10:55.155 --> 10:56.990
I came home early.

10:57.024 --> 11:00.293
Oh. You mean
you were fired again?

11:00.327 --> 11:02.863
Just to be clear,

11:02.896 --> 11:04.765
no wife of mine is running drugs

11:04.798 --> 11:06.333
for Alberto Bravo.

11:06.366 --> 11:08.268
I'm trying
to make money, Carlos,

11:08.301 --> 11:09.903
get us out of this hell hole.

11:09.937 --> 11:11.739
Well, then, you'll
wind up in jail.

11:11.772 --> 11:14.107
I'm already in jail.

11:16.143 --> 11:18.078
I am in charge of this family!

11:18.111 --> 11:19.980
Now, get me a beer.

11:20.013 --> 11:22.115
Please.

11:23.751 --> 11:26.186
Okay.

11:26.219 --> 11:28.121
You did say please.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.505
[cries out]

11:45.538 --> 11:46.974
[growling]

11:49.777 --> 11:52.145
[crashing]

11:57.851 --> 11:59.953
[grunts intensely]

12:02.222 --> 12:04.357
Get up!

12:04.391 --> 12:07.260
I want you gone
before my boys get home!

12:07.294 --> 12:09.396
And if you ever come back...

12:09.429 --> 12:11.198
You crazy bitch.

12:11.231 --> 12:13.166
Get out!

12:15.803 --> 12:18.471
♪ ♪

12:38.091 --> 12:41.061
♪ ♪

12:58.846 --> 13:01.248
This woman
is gonna make us rich.

13:01.281 --> 13:03.316
She's amazing...

13:03.350 --> 13:05.618
♪ ♪

13:09.489 --> 13:12.125
♪ ♪

13:13.326 --> 13:17.797
♪ ♪

13:27.074 --> 13:29.309
♪ ♪

14:17.257 --> 14:19.159
Let's get a drink.

14:24.331 --> 14:26.266
You're quite a dancer.

14:26.299 --> 14:28.301
Thank you.

14:28.335 --> 14:30.003
I'm Caroline.

14:30.037 --> 14:32.539
Carolina.

14:32.572 --> 14:35.208
What shall we
toast to, Carolina?

14:35.242 --> 14:37.510
The good life.

14:37.544 --> 14:40.180
May we all live the good life.

14:51.024 --> 14:52.592
Look at that face.

14:54.261 --> 14:56.196
Beautiful.

15:00.467 --> 15:03.603
A face that deserves
the good life.

15:05.172 --> 15:07.574
♪ ♪

15:13.981 --> 15:16.716
Griselda and Alberto
made good partners...

15:16.749 --> 15:21.221
in crime and otherwise.

15:21.254 --> 15:24.424
He had the connections,
she had the ideas...

15:24.457 --> 15:28.228
like a permanent light bulb
above her head.

15:28.261 --> 15:31.498
Every day,
she found new inspiration,

15:31.531 --> 15:34.667
like using senior citizens
to smuggle a few kilos,

15:34.701 --> 15:38.005
knowing
they'd never get searched.

15:38.038 --> 15:39.206
The wheelchair was a nice touch.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.280
And she went back to Medellín,

15:47.314 --> 15:50.283
only now she was the one
calling the shots.

15:56.723 --> 15:59.959
She oversaw every single detail.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.496
She teamed up
with a local supplier

16:03.530 --> 16:05.665
who was making
quite a name for himself...

16:05.698 --> 16:08.201
Pablo Escobar.

16:09.636 --> 16:12.105
It was the early days
for both of them,

16:12.139 --> 16:15.142
but the money was pouring in.

16:15.175 --> 16:18.011
Pablo had the coke...

16:20.613 --> 16:22.382
but it was
Griselda's inventiveness

16:22.415 --> 16:25.418
that got it across the border.

16:27.620 --> 16:30.190
Bravo.

16:34.161 --> 16:36.463
♪ ♪

16:59.319 --> 17:02.289
Her little boys
had become teenagers.

17:07.727 --> 17:09.229
She moved uptown

17:09.262 --> 17:11.464
to a spacious new apartment.

17:12.865 --> 17:15.367
And to manage all of this,

17:15.402 --> 17:18.838
she had help...

17:18.871 --> 17:21.308
Carolina.

17:30.250 --> 17:31.351
Hey.

17:31.384 --> 17:32.619
Hey.

17:34.654 --> 17:37.090
I'm sorry.
I was hoping not to wake you.

17:37.124 --> 17:39.459
It's all right.

17:39.492 --> 17:41.694
So how was Medellín?

17:41.728 --> 17:44.664
It could not have gone better.

17:44.697 --> 17:47.134
You saved me...

17:47.167 --> 17:48.601
again.

17:48.635 --> 17:50.503
Thank you, Carolina.

17:50.537 --> 17:54.274
Honestly, I don't
mind watching them.

17:54.307 --> 17:56.209
I love those boys.

17:56.243 --> 17:59.146
So how were they?

18:01.181 --> 18:02.682
The principal called.

18:02.715 --> 18:03.716
Twice.

18:03.750 --> 18:05.118
Twice?

18:05.152 --> 18:06.353
Uber, of course,
has been a dream.

18:06.386 --> 18:08.388
I'm not worried about Uber.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.423
But Dixon's been
skipping class again

18:10.457 --> 18:12.392
and going to the tracks.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.627
[sighs] What is it
with those stupid horses?

18:14.661 --> 18:15.895
And he's been taking bets

18:15.928 --> 18:17.430
from his classmates, so...

18:17.464 --> 18:18.598
No.

18:18.631 --> 18:21.401
One more time,
and he's suspended.

18:22.635 --> 18:25.405
Mm. And Osvaldo?

18:27.507 --> 18:29.342
With so little muscle,
I was hoping for some brain.

18:30.677 --> 18:31.844
The thing about Osvaldo

18:31.878 --> 18:34.181
is he's still failing
sixth-grade math.

18:34.214 --> 18:35.648
No, he's in the eighth grade.

18:35.682 --> 18:37.450
I know.

18:39.586 --> 18:42.722
All their father's genes.

18:45.558 --> 18:47.660
I don't want to hear any more.

18:49.696 --> 18:51.398
All right, well...

18:52.799 --> 18:54.701
[packages crinkle]

18:57.804 --> 18:59.572
What are you doing?

18:59.606 --> 19:01.874
You have people
to do that for you.

19:01.908 --> 19:04.511
The girl never showed,
so I had to do it.

19:04.544 --> 19:05.878
Easy as pie.

19:05.912 --> 19:08.415
No, no, no. Promise me
you'll stop doing that.

19:08.448 --> 19:09.616
I mean it.

19:09.649 --> 19:10.817
I mean, if you go to prison...

19:10.850 --> 19:11.784
what...

19:11.818 --> 19:14.187
Okay.

19:14.221 --> 19:16.189
I promise.

19:17.590 --> 19:18.791
You may be the only one

19:18.825 --> 19:21.328
that actually cares
about me, Carolina.

19:21.361 --> 19:23.230
That's not true.

19:24.864 --> 19:28.501
I'll always take care of you.
You know that, right?

19:31.604 --> 19:33.440
[Uber]: Mom?

19:33.473 --> 19:35.975
Is that you?

19:36.008 --> 19:37.710
[Griselda]:
My love...

19:37.744 --> 19:39.446
Oh.

19:39.479 --> 19:41.581
Why are you awake, my love?

19:41.614 --> 19:43.383
It's not very late.

19:43.416 --> 19:45.618
Oh, it's late.
Let's go back to bed.

19:47.387 --> 19:51.291
You made the honors list again!

19:51.324 --> 19:52.992
Oh!

19:53.025 --> 19:54.894
I love you so much.

19:56.363 --> 19:57.897
You'll be the first
in our family

19:57.930 --> 19:59.332
to graduate college.

19:59.366 --> 20:01.468
I'm gonna be
the first in our family

20:01.501 --> 20:02.602
to graduate high school.

20:02.635 --> 20:03.703
[laughing]

20:03.736 --> 20:04.771
Say "uncle", bean pole!

20:04.804 --> 20:05.838
Hey! Enough!

20:05.872 --> 20:07.707
He's gonna pass out!
Dixon!

20:07.740 --> 20:10.610
You two... out of my sight!

20:10.643 --> 20:11.744
Go!

20:14.381 --> 20:16.449
Have a good day, my love.

20:18.351 --> 20:19.786
Mm...

20:19.819 --> 20:22.955
You... if I hear
you're at the track today,

20:22.989 --> 20:24.691
I'll choke you myself.

20:24.724 --> 20:25.758
And you?

20:25.792 --> 20:28.528
Ay. Just go.

20:31.731 --> 20:34.334
One more, one more, one more.

20:38.505 --> 20:40.540
♪ ♪

20:55.955 --> 20:58.991
What the hell?
Who did this?

20:59.025 --> 21:00.259
Boys!

21:01.361 --> 21:02.662
Where is it?

21:02.695 --> 21:05.332
Mama, calm down.
It's all here.

21:05.365 --> 21:08.635
Huh? What have I told you
about going behind that fridge?

21:08.668 --> 21:09.902
Where's Uber?

21:09.936 --> 21:11.638
He's at football
practice. He's fine.

21:11.671 --> 21:14.774
Okay, you have
about two seconds.

21:14.807 --> 21:16.008
We figured out th...

21:16.042 --> 21:17.344
It's in the suitcase.

21:17.377 --> 21:19.011
She's supposed
to guess, you idiot.

21:19.045 --> 21:20.947
Knife, please.

21:29.088 --> 21:30.323
Behold,

21:30.357 --> 21:31.758
the false-bottom suitcase!

21:34.994 --> 21:37.597
Well, shit.

21:37.630 --> 21:39.366
Here's the thing, Mama.

21:39.399 --> 21:41.000
We're not going back to school.

21:41.033 --> 21:41.968
What?

21:42.001 --> 21:43.403
We want to work for you.

21:43.436 --> 21:44.904
Are you insane?
You're kids.

21:44.937 --> 21:45.972
Exactly.

21:46.005 --> 21:47.574
It's a perfect cover.

21:47.607 --> 21:49.342
And since you're
marrying Alberto...

21:49.376 --> 21:51.611
Boys need a father.
A proper one.

21:51.644 --> 21:53.513
It can be a family enterprise.

21:53.546 --> 21:55.815
I escaped Colombia
to come to the United States

21:55.848 --> 21:59.085
so that you and you
could get an education.

21:59.118 --> 22:00.086
Leave that to Uber.

22:00.119 --> 22:01.688
I said no!

22:01.721 --> 22:04.056
Fine. I'll keep up
my side business at school.

22:04.090 --> 22:05.658
And maybe Osvaldo

22:05.692 --> 22:07.059
will learn to read
by the time he graduates.

22:07.093 --> 22:09.996
You don't talk to me like this!

22:14.133 --> 22:17.737
♪ ♪

22:34.186 --> 22:37.757
♪ ♪

22:46.132 --> 22:50.102
♪ ♪

23:01.981 --> 23:04.417
♪ ♪

23:07.987 --> 23:09.155
[Griselda clapping]

23:09.188 --> 23:10.623
Hey!

23:10.657 --> 23:12.825
Shall we see who
is getting married next?

23:12.859 --> 23:15.695
Okay, give me your shoes!
Quick, quick, quick!

23:15.728 --> 23:18.531
This is so exciting!

23:18.565 --> 23:20.099
Quick, quick, quick,
quick, quick, quick.

23:20.132 --> 23:21.734
Okay. Enough, enough.

23:21.768 --> 23:23.035
Okay.

23:23.069 --> 23:24.471
Close my eyes...

23:24.504 --> 23:26.773
And...

23:26.806 --> 23:29.842
The lucky groom is...

23:29.876 --> 23:31.544
[chuckles]

23:31.578 --> 23:32.845
No.

23:32.879 --> 23:34.146
[laughter]

23:34.180 --> 23:35.615
No, no, no, no, no.

23:35.648 --> 23:37.717
Another one.

23:39.819 --> 23:41.020
The lucky groom!

23:41.053 --> 23:42.121
Hey!

23:42.154 --> 23:44.991
[cheering]

23:46.559 --> 23:49.962
♪ ♪

24:10.082 --> 24:13.986
♪ ♪

24:32.572 --> 24:35.708
♪ ♪

24:49.021 --> 24:51.824
♪ ♪

25:02.969 --> 25:06.573
♪ ♪

25:21.821 --> 25:24.156
♪ ♪

25:44.043 --> 25:46.879
♪ ♪

25:56.623 --> 25:59.125
♪ ♪

26:13.706 --> 26:15.975
♪ ♪

26:41.367 --> 26:44.771
This is the wedding gift
I really wanted.

26:49.842 --> 26:52.244
♪ ♪

27:13.399 --> 27:16.035
Now, this is where I come in.

27:16.068 --> 27:17.269
We got wind

27:17.303 --> 27:20.106
there was a new player on scene.

27:20.139 --> 27:21.874
She had dozens
of distribution shops

27:21.908 --> 27:24.677
around the city,

27:24.711 --> 27:26.212
and she was moving
way more product

27:26.245 --> 27:27.980
than we could possibly track.

27:28.014 --> 27:29.081
[crashing]

27:34.053 --> 27:36.088
Freeze!

27:54.340 --> 27:57.910
You sure have been flying
a lot lately, hmm?

28:00.947 --> 28:04.283
Oh, would you look at that?

28:04.316 --> 28:07.854
Here I thought you were selling
Colombian vacuums door to door.

28:11.791 --> 28:14.226
Got at least 50 back there.

28:14.260 --> 28:17.864
50 Ks?
[whistles]

28:17.897 --> 28:22.034
You've certainly been
a busy little bee.

28:22.068 --> 28:24.036
All right, let's save some time.

28:24.070 --> 28:25.504
Although, 50 Ks?

28:25.537 --> 28:28.307
I mean, all you really have
is time, isn't it?

28:28.340 --> 28:30.442
Give me a name.

28:41.120 --> 28:43.155
I don't have a name.

28:43.189 --> 28:44.323
[girl whimpering]

28:44.356 --> 28:47.459
Shh, shh, shh.

28:47.493 --> 28:49.361
You're making
your girlfriend cry.

28:49.395 --> 28:51.964
Por favor deje de.

28:51.998 --> 28:53.432
No una palabra.

28:53.465 --> 28:57.069
[sobbing softly]

28:57.103 --> 28:59.438
Aqui, aqui!

29:10.883 --> 29:13.820
She doesn't know anything,

29:13.853 --> 29:16.889
and even if she did,
she wouldn't tell you.

29:16.923 --> 29:19.158
They'd kill her family.

29:19.191 --> 29:21.493
I'm already a dead man.

29:21.527 --> 29:23.562
Yeah, that you are.

29:23.595 --> 29:26.365
So why don't you
give me something, mm?

29:26.398 --> 29:29.101
I don't want some
low-level bullshit clerk.

29:29.135 --> 29:30.803
I want a real player.

29:33.039 --> 29:34.340
Tell me his name.

29:36.575 --> 29:39.345
Griselda.

29:39.378 --> 29:41.380
They call her La Madrina.

29:45.017 --> 29:47.053
A woman?

29:51.490 --> 29:54.060
♪ ♪

29:54.093 --> 29:56.262
[pho rings]

29:58.330 --> 30:00.399
[ringing]

30:02.468 --> 30:03.870
Yes?

30:03.903 --> 30:05.371
You have to run.

30:05.404 --> 30:06.538
They have Julio!
[panting]

30:06.572 --> 30:08.207
[shouts] Now!

30:08.240 --> 30:11.077
♪ ♪

30:15.014 --> 30:16.182
[Griselda]:
Hurry! Let's go!

30:16.215 --> 30:17.516
I know! I know!

30:22.221 --> 30:24.223
Quick!

30:24.256 --> 30:25.124
Alberto! Move it!

30:25.157 --> 30:26.993
The van's ready!

30:27.026 --> 30:30.229
♪ ♪

30:34.433 --> 30:35.834
Go! Go, go, go, go!

30:37.569 --> 30:39.838
Let's go. Let's go!

30:42.008 --> 30:44.110
♪ ♪

30:44.143 --> 30:45.511
Ready? Let's go.

30:49.581 --> 30:52.885
The woman was smart,

30:52.919 --> 30:54.286
and when I thought I was close,

30:54.320 --> 30:56.122
she was always a step ahead...

30:58.590 --> 31:00.326
heading to another safe house.

31:00.359 --> 31:03.129
She had 'em all over the city.

31:06.999 --> 31:09.035
